European transport authorities need a data-driven way to classify annual passenger transport activity for each country into meaningful operational categories. The dataset provided (estat_ttr00015.tsv) contains yearly passenger-kilometres (million PKM) for multiple European countries from 2013 to 2024.

The goal of this project is to build a supervised classification model that assigns each country-year record into one of three transport trend categories:

Classification Labels

Decline â€“ A year where transport activity decreases beyond a defined threshold.

Normal/Stable â€“ Minor fluctuations within expected year-to-year variation.

Recovery/Growth â€“ A year where transport activity increases significantly following a previous decline.

ğŸ¯ Business Objectives

This model will help policymakers and transport authorities:

Detect Transport Decline Early â†’ enabling targeted intervention programs.

Monitor Post-Crisis Recovery (e.g., post-COVID transport patterns).

Allocate Budget & Infrastructure Investments based on classified trends.

Improve Accuracy of Transport Forecasting Models by incorporating trend categories as input features.

ğŸ“ Trend Classification Logic (Explicit Thresholds)

Thresholds will be calculated using % change year-to-year for each country:

Decline: Transport activity decreases by â‰¥ 5% compared to previous year

Normal: Change between -5% and +5%

Recovery/Growth: Increase of â‰¥ 5%, OR two or more consecutive increases

(Thresholds can be adjusted based on domain expert feedback.)

